<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06104101 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06104101 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PAST; PRESIDENT; SPOUSE; BOOK; CONTROVERSY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  SLEAZE sells. Big time.;    Kitty Kelley's down-and-dirty unauthorizedbiography of former first lady Nancy Reagan is a certified publishingphenomenon. Simon andamp; Schuster says it has taken 516,000 re-orders frombookstores and wholesalers -- which means there are now nearly a millioncopies of the book in print (925,000, to be precise). The book was justreleased Monday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Living  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  BUT IT'S SELLING LIKE CRAZY  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  See also related story on this page.  </MEMO><TEXT>     Martha Whittier, the public relations agent who handled Kelley's West Coastpublicity, said Friday that is &quot;an unprecedented rate of sales&quot; for a firstweek.;    The book is so big, in fact, that the author apparently has decidedthe book doesn't need any more hype. Kelley on Friday downgraded herpromotional tour to a series of satellite interviews -- canceling interviewswith Larry King, among others.;    Victoria Meyer, spokeswoman for Simon andamp;Schuster, said: &quot;I can't imagine she isn't exhausted. She has remarkableresilience and energy, but anybody would be exhausted and stunned by what hashappened.&quot;;    Meanwhile, the Reagans' daughter Patti Davis is cashing in onthe excitement caused by Kelley's book by pushing up the publication date ofher new tome.;    She describes it as the story of a girl who is &quot;deeplyaffected by a psychologically domineering mother.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  HOLLY HAYES, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910413  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  207  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday April 13, 1991